olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">very Elon Musk corporate governance</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk is asking users of X whether Tesla Inc. should =
invest $5 billion in his artificial intelligence startup, saying he was =E2=
=80=9Ctesting the waters=E2=80=9D for a potential transaction.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Tesla chief executive officer posed the question s=
hortly after the carmaker reported a fourth straight quarter of disappointi=
ng profit. Musk was asked during the earnings call if the company would inv=
est in xAI or integrate its chat bot, called Grok, into Tesla=E2=80=99s sof=
tware.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CTesla is learning quite a b=
it from xAI,=E2=80=9D Musk said, adding that it had helped advance Full Sel=
f-Driving, the suite of driver-assistance features that do not make Tesla=
=E2=80=99s vehicles autonomous. He said he supported the idea of Tesla inve=
sting in xAI, if shareholders approved it, then posted a poll on the matter=
 late Tuesday.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I love that Mus=
k wants to invest the money of one company he runs (Tesla) into another com=
pany he owns (xAI), so he=E2=80=99s asking the customers of a third company=
 he owns (X) to vote on it. What do X users have to do with Tesla? The answ=
er might be something like =E2=80=9Cthe entire Elon Musk corporate complex =
is increasingly defined by personal fandom for Elon Musk, so an X poll prob=
ably=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a decent proxy for what Tesla shareholders want.=
=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Though probably=C2=A0the answer i=
s =E2=80=9Cthis is just for fun.=E2=80=9D Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36172030.194392/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVy=
LmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTgxNTkwNzg0NDQzNDExMjk5OQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB33bdbd14" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">the poll</a>, which is unusually lawyered for Musk: =
=E2=80=9CShould Tesla invest $5B into=C2=A0@xAI, assuming the valuation is =
set by several credible outside investors? (Board approval &amp; shareholde=
r vote are needed, so this is just to test the waters).=E2=80=9D Third-part=
y valuation! Board approval! (Special committee of independent director app=
roval? Ehh maybe?) Shareholder approval! Not that long ago, Musk would have=
 just=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3617203=
0.194392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMD=
QtMjgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXMtb3RoZXItbWVyZ2VyLXdvcmtlZC1vdXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyNDI0X=
01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rl=
cm09MjQwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2e55e=
00b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">had Tesla buy companies he owned at valuations set by him</a>,=
 so this seems like a chastened, responsible Elon Musk.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Also: <em>shareholder</em>=C2=A0approval?=C2=A0<em>In general<=
/em>, a company with an equity market cap of almost $700 billion would not=
=C2=A0<em>hold a shareholder vote=C2=A0</em>to make a $5 billion investment=
. But I assume the point here is that, if you are doing a transaction with =
a conflict of interest (like investing Tesla=E2=80=99s money in a private c=
ompany owned by its chief executive officer), you will get sued, and it is =
helpful to be able to say =E2=80=9Cno, this transaction is fine, see, the i=
ndependent shareholders approved it.=E2=80=9D Or at least that is <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36172030.194392/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDItMDEvdGV4YXMtdGVt=
