ing people.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If they ask you =E2=80=
=9Chow much does this hammer cost,=E2=80=9D and you can tell by looking at =
them that they are savvy about hammer prices and willing to walk a block to=
 the other store, you will tell them a competitive price.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If they ask you =E2=80=9Chow much does this hammer=
 cost,=E2=80=9D and you can tell by looking at them that they have plenty o=
f money, are insensitive to price and don=E2=80=99t know there=E2=80=99s an=
other hardware store nearby, you will smoothly say =E2=80=9Cthat hammer is =
$50=E2=80=9D and they=E2=80=99ll pay you.</li></ul><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Is that an=C2=A0<em>antitrust violation?=C2=A0</em>I feel like the tra=
ditional answer is =E2=80=9Cno, of course not=E2=80=9D: You are not a monop=
olist, there=E2=80=99s another competitor nearby, you are just good at busi=
ness. On the other hand, if <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/36172030.194392/aHR0cHM6Ly9yZXBvc2l0b3J5Lmxhdy51bWljaC5lZHUvY2dpL=
3ZpZXdjb250ZW50LmNnaT9yZWZlcmVyPSZodHRwc3JlZGlyPTEmYXJ0aWNsZT0yNTQ5JmNvbnRl=
