qZWN0aXZlJTIwb2YlMjBVLlMuJTIwYW50aXRydXN0JTIwbGF3Lg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB13f17a06" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">the purpose of antitrust regulation</a> is to keep cons=
umer prices low, there=E2=80=99s something a bit unsettling about this: You=
 don=E2=80=99t have monopoly power, but you do have the power to charge sup=
racompetitive prices, which is kind of the bad thing people are worried abo=
ut.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Technology seems to be moving toward pe=
rfect price discrimination, and the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/36172030.194392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9md=
